THE vice chairman of Lobi Stars Football Club of Makurdi Tama Aondofa said he has made welfare of players and staff as his priority since taking over the affairs of the club in the middle of the Nigeria Professional Football League. Speaking with journalist after his team thrash Heartland FC of Owerri 3- 0 at Aper Aku Stadium in Makurdi in a midweek encounter , Mr. Tama noted that once players and officials welfare are talking care ,playing on the field in made easy. He stated that since taking over the Makurdi Premier League club sideÂ  , he has introduced some reforms aimed at repositioning the club for better performance and everything is working according to plan.